  "bio": [
    "Christian Sinding is a private equity executive and former CEO of EQT, one of the world's largest PE firms.",
    "He joined EQT in 1998 after working as a consultant at McKinsey & Company.",
    "Sinding spent more than two decades helping build EQT into a global buyout powerhouse with investments across Europe, North America and Asia.",
    "He became CEO in 2019, the same year EQT went public on the Stockholm Stock Exchange.",
    "He stepped down as CEO in 2025, and was succeeded by fellow billionaire Per Franzén."
